![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The `rename` function does not validate whether the new name already exists in the database. Since the `name` column in the `keyboard_layouts` table has a unique constraint, attempting to rename a layout to an existing name will throw a `SQLiteConstraintException` and crash the app.

You should use the existing `repository.nameExists` method to check for name collisions (excluding the current layout ID) before performing the rename.

```kotlin
    fun rename(layoutId: Long, newName: String) {
        viewModelScope.launch {
            val trimmed = newName.trim()
            if (!repository.nameExists(trimmed, layoutId)) {
                repository.rename(layoutId, trimmed)
            }
        }
    }
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The modifier checkbox labels `"Ctrl"`, `"Alt"`, and `"Shift"` are hardcoded in English. To support proper internationalization, you should use the existing string resources `R.string.button_key_ctrl`, `R.string.button_key_alt`, and `R.string.button_key_shift`.

```suggestion
                        ModifierCheckbox(stringResource(R.string.button_key_ctrl), ctrl) { ctrl = it }
                        ModifierCheckbox(stringResource(R.string.button_key_alt), alt) { alt = it }
                        ModifierCheckbox(stringResource(R.string.button_key_shift), shift) { shift = it }
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The modifier prefix strings `"Ctrl+"`, `"Alt+"`, and `"Shift+"` are hardcoded in English. Since `keyDescription` is a `@Composable` function, you can use `stringResource` to retrieve the localized modifier names.

```kotlin
        if (spec.ctrl) append(stringResource(R.string.button_key_ctrl) + "+")
        if (spec.alt) append(stringResource(R.string.button_key_alt) + "+")
        if (spec.shift) append(stringResource(R.string.button_key_shift) + "+")
```

